# IMP-0200

# Hypervisor Service Interfaces

Status: Draft

Version: 0.1

Depends on:

* RFC-0020 Hypervisor Architecture
* RFC-0021 Hypervisor Scheduling Engine
* RFC-0022 Provider Interface
* IMP-0003 Internal Event Bus
* IMP-0100 Persistence Model

---

# 1. Purpose

This document defines the primary service interfaces of the AiDN Hypervisor.

Business logic SHALL depend exclusively on these interfaces.

Concrete implementations remain interchangeable.

---

# 2. Design Principles

### IF-1

Every service exposes exactly one primary interface.

---

### IF-2

Services communicate only through interfaces or immutable events.

---

### IF-3

Implementations SHALL NOT depend on other implementations.

Only interfaces.

---

### IF-4

Every interface SHALL support mocking for unit testing.

---

# 3. Endpoint Service

Responsible for Endpoint lifecycle.

```go id="xyn9v6"
type EndpointService interface {

    CreateEndpoint(ctx context.Context, cmd CreateEndpointCommand) (CreateEndpointResult, error)

    UpdateEndpoint(ctx context.Context, cmd UpdateEndpointCommand) (UpdateEndpointResult, error)

    DeleteEndpoint(ctx context.Context, cmd DeleteEndpointCommand) (DeleteEndpointResult, error)

    StartEndpoint(ctx context.Context, cmd StartEndpointCommand) (StartEndpointResult, error)

    StopEndpoint(ctx context.Context, cmd StopEndpointCommand) (StopEndpointResult, error)

    SuspendEndpoint(ctx context.Context, cmd SuspendEndpointCommand) (SuspendEndpointResult, error)

    ResumeEndpoint(ctx context.Context, cmd ResumeEndpointCommand) (ResumeEndpointResult, error)

    GetEndpoint(ctx context.Context, cmd GetEndpointCommand) (GetEndpointResult, error)

    ListEndpoints(ctx context.Context, cmd ListEndpointsCommand) (ListEndpointsResult, error)
}
```

---

# 4. Bundle Service

Responsible for Bundle lifecycle.

```go id="g8u0f8"
type BundleService interface {

