# 14. Common Rules

Every service SHALL:

* own its own persistence;
* own its own events;
* expose only one primary interface;
* remain independently testable.

---

# 15. Dependency Graph

```text id="sln4os"
API

↓

Endpoint

↓

Scheduler

↓

Runtime

↓

Provider

↓

Hardware
```

Dependencies MAY point only downward.

Circular dependencies are prohibited.

---

# 16. Construction

Every service SHALL be instantiated through dependency injection.

Services SHALL NOT create other services directly.

Construction SHALL occur only during Hypervisor bootstrap.

---

# 17. Testing

Every service SHALL provide:

* unit tests;
* mock implementation;
* integration tests.

Mock implementations SHALL satisfy the same interfaces as production implementations.

---

# 18. Design Invariants

Invariant 1

Interfaces define architecture.

Implementations define behavior.

---

Invariant 2

Services depend only on interfaces.

---

Invariant 3

Dependency injection is mandatory.

---

Invariant 4

Every operation SHALL use exactly one Command object and exactly one Result object.

---

Invariant 5

Primitive parameter lists are prohibited.

---

Invariant 6

Every dependency SHALL be explicit.
